ResourcePool::Resource::Net::LDAP - Net::LDAP bindings for ResourcePool

Copyright (c) 2001-2003 by Markus Winand <mws@fatalmind.com>

See COPYRIGHT section in the ResourcePool::Resource::Net::LDAP(3pm) manpage.

Recent Changes
--------------
  *  Export of ':all' from Net::LDAP::Constants has been replaced by 
     the actually required constants only. 

Installation
------------
    This modules requires ResourcePool to be pre installed.
    ResourcePool and this package are a pure perl implemented
    modules and should therefore run everywhere where perl is
    already installed.

    The well known procedure is:
        perl Makefile.PL
        make
        make test
        make install 

Examples
--------
    Are included in the manpages which come with this distribution.
    To start with ResourcePool read the ResourcePool::BigPicture(3pm)
    manpage, to learn something about the Net::LDAP bindings included
    in this package visit the ResourcePool::Factory::Net::LDAP(3pm) manpage.

Obtaining the most recent version
---------------------------------
    This package and subsequent updates is available on CPAN. Please
    use a mirror close to you when downloading from CPAN.

        http://www.cpan.org/SITES.html

How to contribute?
------------------
    Submit patches for bugs you discovered (or report the at least),
    upload your own resource bindings to CPAN.

